{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Altmeyer et al.",
    "[60,61] develop scalable techniques for single-path programs, improving precision and scalability by considering relevant memory blocks and cache contention.",
    "Lesage et al. [62] adapt these techniques for multipath programs, introducing conservative join functions and worst-case execution path expansion to handle complex control flows.",
    "Chen et al. [63] use a non-homogeneous Markov chain to model set-associative caches, further improving SPTA methods.In addition, in addressing the challenges of deriving trustworthy probabilistic WCET estimates for software running on complex processors, Vilardell et al.",
    "[64] highlight the limitations of Extreme Value Theory (EVT) [65], which introduces both model and statistical uncertainties."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "[60,61] develop scalable techniques for single-path programs, improving precision and scalability by considering relevant memory blocks and cache contention.",
